<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-accounts-payable-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who runs it</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor runs your payables &mdash; you keep the approval.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The value of A/P management isn&rsquo;t pushing payments out the door &mdash; it&rsquo;s everything that has to be right before they go: bills recorded accurately, due dates tracked, the aging kept current, duplicates and already-paid bills caught, W-9s on file, and the payable balance reconciled to your books. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope, inside your own QuickBooks file, and presents each payment run for your approval. We record and prepare; <strong>you authorize</strong> &mdash; we do not move your money without your approval. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

